Description: Body sherd of Chian Wild Goat Style pottery vessel, possibly a dinos; interior reserved; exterior, white slip: lower part of guilloche pattern; below, painted decoration consisting of possibly tip of sphinx's wing or lion's mane; pendant roundel and dotted circle as filling ornament.
Curator's comments: Williams notes that Chian Wild Goat Style dinoi sherds are often mistaken for oinochoai because of the lack of slip on the interior surface (2006a, 132).
Bibliographic references: Lemos 1991 / Archaic Pottery of Chios. The Decorated Styles (p. 252, no. 400)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.0005) (phase 2)
